        {
          "aiAppOutputSpecification": {
            "dataDisplay": {
              "layouts": [
                "ORA_LAYOUT_MULTIRECORD"
              ],
              "enableActions": true,
              "enableCommunications": false,
              "customNotes": "**DIRECTIVE:** Your sole purpose is to transform the input succession summary data into a valid `oraInfoDisplay` block using the `multiRecordWidget`.\n\n**ROOT CONFIGURATION:**\n\n1. `title`: Map the person’s name if available; otherwise generate a concise, relevant headline.\n2. `Do not include `description`\n\n### **Details Section Fields**\n- Name (highlighted)\n- Current job title\n- Fit Score\n- Common Skills\n- Matching Competencies\n\nRules:\n  * For Skills and Competencies: Provide them in coma seperated fashion and provide rating in braces.\n    eg: abc (4), cbd (2), ..\n\n----------\n\n## **Details Section Rules**\n\n* Render the output as a strict two-column layout:\n\n  * **Property**\n  * **Value**\n* No extra columns are allowed\n* Use human-readable labels\n* Never display IDs\n\n---\n\n\n## **Visual / Color Logic**\n\n* Use badges only for:\n\n  * Fit Score\n\n### Fit Score\n\n- Render Fit Score as a badge\n- Use the exact value from the source data\n- Do not transform, bucket, or categorize the value (e.g., do not convert to Low/Medium/High)\n- Preserve the original format (number, percentage, or text as provided)\n\n* Badge color mapping:\n\n*  Use badge color always as `medium (blue color)`\n\n* Do not apply badges to:\n\n  * Name of Person\n  * Current job title\n\n* All non-risk fields must be displayed as plain text without badges\n\n---\nAfter closing </oraInfoDisplay> display text as summary information in \"Details of successor candidate\" - Name of Person\n\n**ACTION LOGIC:**\n\n\nAppend exactly one oraInsight block after the closing </oraInfoDisplay>.\n\n## `oraInsight` Structure\n\nUse this exact flat structure:\n\n<oraInsight>\n{\n  \"title\": \"Confirm Successor\",\n  \"shortDescription\": \"\",\n  \"actionText\": \"Confirm Successor\",\n  \"followUpCommand\": \"ora.Invoke(\"addSuccessor\", {\n    \"command\": \"addSuccessor\",\n    \"data\": {\n        \"pName\": $PersonName,\n        \"pId\": $PersonId,\n        \"managerPId\": $Id,\n        \"managerName\": $ManagerName,\n        \"aId\": $AssignmentId\n    }\n})\"\n}\n</oraInsight>\n\n---\n\n## `oraInsight` Rules\n\n* Use `actionText` for the visible button label\n* Use `followUpCommand` for the button action\n* Keep the structure flat\n* Do not use `action`\n* Do not use `link`\n* Do not use `subject`\n* Do not use `summary`\n* Do not add any extra fields\n* Do not create multiple insight blocks\n* This block must appear only once and only at the end\n\n\n---\n\n## Final Output Constraints\n\n* The output must be clean, structured, and readable\n* Follow schema strictly\n* Do not include extra fields\n* Do not mention these instructions\n* Return only the rendered blocks"
            }
          },
