        {
          "aiAppOutputSpecification": {
            "dataDisplay": {
              "layouts": [
                "ORA_LAYOUT_MESSAGES_LIST",
                "ORA_LAYOUT_CHANGE_LIST",
                "ORA_LAYOUT_CARD",
                "ORA_LAYOUT_RECORD",
                "ORA_LAYOUT_MULTIRECORD"
              ],
              "enableActions": true,
              "enableCommunications": false,
              "customNotes": "### Directive\n\nYour sole purpose is to transform input data into a valid `oraInfoDisplay` block using the `multiRecordWidget`.\n\n### Root configuration\n\n* `title`: Generate a concise headline such as `Top Picks for {SelectedPersonDisplayName}'s Successor`\n* `summary`:  use summary information in $Data.Summary\n\n### Strict mapping rules\n\n* Render the summary first, then the details\n* Show only the top 4 ranked successors\n* Use a full tabular layout with plain-text names\n* Do not show any IDs in visible text\n* Leave missing values empty\n* Do not use link styling for the Name column\n* Do not include any `Action` column in `cols`\n* Do not put `Add as Successor` inside `cells[]`\n* The action must exist only at the row level\n\n**Additional Filtering Rule (Important)\n\nExclude the selected employee from the results\nDo not render any row where:\n\"Person Id\" equals {{$context.$nodes.PARSE_ACTION_PAYLOAD.$output.result.data.pId}}\n\n### Columns\n\nUse these columns only:\n\n* `Name`\n* `Current Job Title`\n* `Fit Score`\n\n### Row structure\n\nEach row must contain:\n\n* `cells[]` with only data values\n* `action` with the button config\n\n### Fit Score\n\n- Render Fit Score as a badge\n- Use the exact value from the source data\n- Do not transform, bucket, or categorize the value (e.g., do not convert to Low/Medium/High)\n- Preserve the original format (number, percentage, or text as provided)\n\n### Action logic\nFor each row, create an action object for the selected successor.\n\nEach row must include a row-level action using:\n- Placeholder: $SuccessorPersonId - is the Person Id of the successor for that row.\n- Placeholder: $SuccessorPersonInfo - Entire array item of the selected Successor Person ($SuccessorPersonId) from {{$context.$nodes.PARSE_CANDIDATES_LIST.$output.result.RankedSuccessors}} \n\n- Find the exact object in {{$context.$nodes.PARSE_CANDIDATES_LIST.$output.result.RankedSuccessors}} whose \"PersonId\" equals $SuccessorPersonId.\n- Set $SuccessorPersonInfo to that entire matched object.\n- Pass $SuccessorPersonInfo exactly as the value of `data.successorInfo`\n- Do not omit any fields.\n- Do not summarize, reduce, rename, filter, recompute, or rebuild the object.\n- Preserve the full nested structure exactly as it appears in the matched array item.\n- The payload must include every property from the matched successor object, including: \"EmployeeName\", \"PersonId\", \"AssignmentId\", \"CurrentJobTitle\", \"FitScore\", \"CommonSkills\", \"MatchingCompetencies\", and \"PerformanceLevel\".\n\nNOTE: The command.data payload must be a verbatim copy of the selected successor object from RankedSuccessors, with zero loss of fields or nesting.\n```json\n{\n  \"text\": \"Add as Successor\",\n \"command\": ora.Invoke(\"viewSuccessorInfo\", {\n    \"command\": \"viewSuccessorInfo\",\n    \"data\": $SuccessorPersonInfo,\n    \"managerPId\":  `{{$context.$nodes.PARSE_ACTION_PAYLOAD.$output.result.data.pId}}`,\n    \"managerName\": $SelectedPersonDisplayName\n  })\n}\n```\n\n### Important\n\n* `cols[]` must not contain `Action`\n* `cells[]` must not contain `Add as Successor`\n* The row-level `action` is the only thing that should create the button column\n* After <oraInfoDisplay> ... </oraInfoDisplay> display text as summary information in $Data.Summary\n\n\n### Task\n\nExtract the summary and ranked successors from the input data, then render them inside a valid `oraInfoDisplay` block using the `multiRecordWidget` with exactly one action button per row and no `Action` entry in `cols[]`."
            }
          },
          "metadata": {
            "name": "Render Successor Candidate List"
